In this article, we learned how to build custom Docker images, 
-run a Spring Boot Application as a Docker container, 
-and create containers with docker-compose.

https://www.baeldung.com/dockerizing-spring-boot-application

COMMANDS:
1 building artifcats :  mvn clean package
2 run artifacts      :  java -jar target/message-server-1.0.0.jar


Docker Command
- docker ps          : list containers
- docker image ls -a : list images


- image creation : docker build --tag=message-server:latest .
- run container  : docker run -p8887:8888 message-server:latest


DOCKER for configuring multiple containers via docker compose file:

-Syntax checking      : docker-compose config
-Build Define Image   : docker-compose up --build
-Remove container     : docker-compose down

